Sec. 143.103. IMMUNITY FROM LIABILITY. A person whose vehicle
strikes, kills, injures, or damages an unattended animal running at
large on a highway is not liable for damages to the animal except as
a finding of:
(1) gross negligence in the operation of the vehicle; or
(2) wilful intent to strike, kill, injure, or damage the
animal.
Acts 1981, 67th Leg., p. 1350, ch. 388, Sec. 1, eff. Sept. 1, 1981.
Statute text rendered on: 8/6/2022

